Source: pgdisablelogerror
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), zlib1g-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/fmbiete/pgdisablelogerror

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pgdisablelogerror
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pgdisablelogerror
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Disable selected SQLSTATE errors from PostgreSQL server logging
 pgdisablelogerror installs an emit_log hook that suppresses server log output
 for configured SQLSTATE error codes. It must be loaded through
 shared_preload_libraries before use.
